rule.description:
Method calls should be used directly in loop conditionals rather than testing inside the loop with a break statement. This makes the loop condition explicit and improves readability.
Use: while (hasMore()) { ... } Instead of: while (true) { if (!hasMore()) { break; } ... }
Version: 1.0.0

rule.example:

// Violation: while(true) with break inside
while (true) {
	if (!hasMore()) {
		break;
	}
	processItem();
}

// Valid: Use method call in loop condition
while (hasMore()) {
	processItem();
}
